    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Consumer Behaviour in Brokerage Industry with Special Reference to Reliance Money in Delhi</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Vikashkumar</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Brokerage Industry<br />Reliance Money</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">1-May-2010 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P4561</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">The main objective in undertaking this project was to supplement academic knowledge with absolute practical exposure to day to day function of an organization
This project consumer behavior in brokerage industry (Delhi) (mutual fund, stock market, insurance)involved detail study of Indian financial market and various investment avenues such as mutual fund and investment.
This project help me to get a deeper understanding of the day to day working and dealing directly with customers and getting various information about the behavior of customers related to brokerage industry with special reference to Reliance money,
The main objective of any financial company would be to provide an absolute tailor made products and services to the customer and to retain them to the organization, But to retain a particular customer is not easy because customer expectation change by time and it becomes a tough job for the company to curve the needs of their customers. Now with the case of asset management company which is getting it space and a lot of company emerging as player here a study has been undertaken with regard to Reliance money where study looks the expectation of the customer regarding Mutual funds, Stock markets and insurance issues related to customer expectation.
The need for this research is to emphasis behavior of customer of mutual fund and how the company in contrast to the expectation is performing.
This research is conducted to understand the customer perception and behavior towards financial products. Till yesterday people are having b=very less knowledge for mutual funds and investments because of brokerage companies in India had not made any efforts tom expand the market. They have been doing business with same customer. There is also a lack of investors awareness as for as market are concerned. Harshad Mehta scam and various other scams had created bad impressions in people mind and this need to be changed. An investment product is a trust that pools the savings of number of investors to share the common financial goals, financial product is most suitable investment for the common man as it offers an opportunity to invest in diversified and managed baskets of securities at a relatively low cost</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/8118">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/8118</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/8042">MBA-2010</a><br/></td></tr>
